<div id="pf5e" class="pf wa h6" data-page-no="5e"><div class="pc pc5e wa h6"><img class="bi x0 y0 wb h7" alt="" src="bg5e.png"/><div class="t m28c x2b h1a y600 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">V. LED BY THE SPIRIT (Luke 1:6; Acts 10:1, 2). </div><div class="t ma6 x48 h1a y86f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m4ab x37 h1a yb93 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Guidance and Power of the Spirit (Luke 12:12; Acts 1:8). </div><div class="t m2eb x48 h1a yb94 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke&apos;s Gospel begins with a great flurry of activity in Jerusalem and </div><div class="t m4aa x2b h1a y604 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nazareth as the Spirit imprints His authority of divine action on events. Acts </div><div class="t m26d x2b h1a y605 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">resounds with the rushing wind of the Spirit as it drives the ship of the faith-</div><div class="t m379 x2b h1a y607 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ful witness ever onward. </div><div class="t mf x48 h1a y608 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke did not present the Spirit as the Giver of Christian character (Gal. </div><div class="t m140 x2b h1a y592 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5:22, 23). He left it to Paul to convey the inner struggle between flesh and </div><div class="t m259 x2b h1a y60b ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Spirit (verses 17, 18). He did, however, capture the essence of the convict-</div><div class="t m49 x2b h1a y361 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ing, converting power of the Spirit (John 16:7-10), and of the Spirit who </div><div class="t m134 x2b h1a yb95 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">guides into truth (14:26). Above all else he knew the Spirit who testifies of </div><div class="t m28 x2b h1a y502 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus through the believer (15:26). </div><div class="t m5d7 x48 h1a yb96 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What purpose does God have in giving the Spirit to every believer? </div><div class="t m1f9 x29 h1a y65f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Acts 2:32, 33; 4:31. </div><div class="t mab x48 h1a y661 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m1a0 x65 h1a ye1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prayer Teaches Obedience and Trust (Luke 22:40, 41; Acts 20:19-</div><div class="t mf6 x29 h1a y5fb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">24). </div><div class="t m5d8 x48 h1a yb97 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How does prayer help us relate to the needs and situation of others? </div><div class="t m4dd x29 h1a y663 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 22:31, 32; Acts 12:4, 5. </div><div class="t m118 x5d h1a y846 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;It is our Lord&apos;s will that we who have received access to these powers </div><div class="t m272 x29 h1a yf3 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through prayer should go through this world transmitting heavenly power to </div><div class="t m5d9 x5c h1a yb98 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">every corner of a world which needs it sorely. Our lives should be, according to </div><div class="t m377 x5c h1a yb99 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">our Lord&apos;s plans, quiet, but steadily flowing, streams of blessing, which </div><div class="t m56d x29 h1a y667 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through our prayers and intercessions should reach our whole environ-</div><div class="t m265 x29 h1a yb1e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ment.&apos; &quot;â€”O. Hallesby, </div><div class="t m5da x45 h1a y36a ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Prayer </div><div class="t m1a7 x9d h1a yb9a ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(London: W. S. Cowell Ltd., 1949), p. 51. </div><div class="t mae x5d h1a yb9b ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m378 x65 h1a y668 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Living According to God&apos;s Law (Luke 10:27, 28; Acts 20:18, 19). </div><div class="t m38f x5d h1a yb9c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke presents a clear picture of the lifestyle expected of the follower of </div><div class="t m157 x5c h1a yb9d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus. The follower will: </div><div class="t m68 x5d h1a yb6e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m26 x65 h1a yb9e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Be obedient to the commandments of God (Luke 1:6; 23:56). </div><div class="t m68 x5d h1a y564 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m260 x65 h1a yb9f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Accept the will of God (Luke 1:35; Acts 5:29). </div><div class="t m68 x5d h1a yba0 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t ma2 x65 h1a yba0 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Keep the Sabbath (Luke 4:16; Acts 17:2). </div><div class="t m68 x5d h1a y23 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t me8 x65 h1a yba1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Be generous and merciful (Luke 6:36-38; Acts 20:35). </div><div class="t m68 x5d h1a y104 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m3e2 x3b h1a yba2 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Be consistent and forgiving (Luke 6:41, 42). </div><div class="t m68 x5d h1a y569 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m109 x3b h1a yba3 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Love God and neighbor (Luke 10:27). </div><div class="t m19b x5d h1a yba4 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How does God expect His church to relate lifestyle to witness? Acts </div><div class="t m531 x5c h1a y108 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9:31; 11:23, 24. </div><div class="t ma0 x5d h1a y4c6 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. Hearing God&apos;s Voice (Luke 24:32; Acts 26:19). </div><div class="t m5db x5d h1a yba5 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">No one could accept Luke and then abandon the Old Testament. The Lord </div><div class="t m4fd x41 h1a yba6 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">directed His disciples to the Old Testament (Luke 24:32, 44); there the </div><div class="t m1ab x41 h29 yba7 ff2 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">94 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
